			<ns0:name>robe...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/108771824208521698652/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Ack. mseaborn raise a similar concern.

My changes right now aim at getting our *scons build* to use extensions consistently.
There is no equivalent for '.pexe' in the real world so it should be fine fixing this.
The .bc and .o story is, of course, different.

Going forward I am not sure what the right thing to do is. 
Other platforms (e.g. windows) use .obj and .dll and I would hope that autotools would be flexible enough to deal with non-unix extensions, scons is.
Hopefully, the self-build of llvm will give us enough experience to make a call.

